# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation only
#   style    - Formatting, no code change
#   refactor - Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf     - Performance improvement
#   test     - Adding or updating tests
#   build    - Build system or dependencies
#   ci       - CI configuration
#   chore    - Other changes (e.g., updating .gitignore)
#   revert   - Revert a previous commit
#
# Scope (optional): component affected (e.g., desktop, daemon, shared)
#
# Subject: imperative, lowercase, no period at end
#
# Examples:
#   feat(desktop): add dark mode toggle
#   fix(daemon): resolve memory leak in sync service
#   docs: update installation instructions
#   refactor(shared): simplify type definitions
#
# Breaking changes: add ! after type/scope
#   feat!: redesign authentication flow
#   fix(api)!: change response format
